article.description: James Thompson IV hit 7 of 13 field goals and finished with 19 points and a career-high 15 rebounds, while Brandon Nazione added 16 and 11 to help Eastern Michigan beat Central Michigan 71-56 Tue
article.headline: Thompson IV, Eastern Michigan beat Central Michigan 71-56
article.linkText: Thompson IV, Eastern Michigan beat Central Michigan 71-56
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- James Thompson IV hit 7 of 13 field goals and finished with 19 points and a career-high 15 rebounds, while Brandon Nazione added 16 and 11 to help Eastern Michigan beat Central Michigan 71-56 Tuesday night. Ty Toney scored 11 and Tim Bond added 10 points with five assists for Eastern Michigan. Nazione made a layup, then hit a 3-pointer to cap a 13-2 run to open the game and the Eagles (12-12, 4-7 Mid-American Conference) never trailed. Central Michigan (13-11, 6-5) scored 12 of the next 14 points to pull within one with nine minutes left in the first half, but Eastern Michigan responded with a 20-4 spurt that pushed its lead to 17 before going into halftime up 38-23. Chris Fowler converted a 3-point play that cut the Chippewas' deficit to seven with five minutes left, but they would get no closer. Fowler led CMU with 16 points.
